    "description": "<h3>Obtaining Demonic Powers</h3><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">There are three ways to obtain the powers of a demon:</span></p><ul><li><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>By trading them:</strong> You agree to perform a service or offer something of value to the demon in exchange for its powers. Once the service has been rendered (or a promise made to render the service made), you can obtain the demon's powers.</span></p></li><li><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>By stealing them:</strong> If you have the Rogue class, you can choose to steal a demon's powers instead of their spiritual treasure or IP.</span></p></li><li><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>By extorting them:</strong> When you personally reduce a demon to 0 HP, instead of describing how you put this demon out of play you can leave this narration to the GM, demanding that this demon offer you their powers in exchange.</span></p></li></ul><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Note the demon's weaknesses, resistances, immunities, absorptions and traits. Demons can't take back the powers you've obtained from them (even if you don't keep your promises).</span></p>",
